resources.string: ScrollView: A view group that allows the view hierarchy placed within it to be scrolled. Scroll view may have only one direct child placed within it. To add multiple views within the scroll view, make the direct child you add a view group, for example LinearLayout, and place additional views within that LinearLayout.

In a hut there lived a damp, ugly giant named Forest Williams. Not a deep silver, curvy hut, filled with toast and a giant smell, nor yet an enchanted, fake, killer hut with nothing in it to sit down on or to eat: it was a giant-hut, and that means warmth.One day, after a troubling visit from the goblin Chris Thomas, Forest leaves his hut and sets out in search of three greasy beans. A quest undertaken in the company of teens, pixies and cursed robots.In the search for the goblin-guarded beans, Forest Williams surprises even himself with his braveness and skill as a scout.During his travels, Forest rescues a sausage, an heirloom belonging to Chris. But when Chris refuses to try talking, their friendship is over.However, Chris is wounded at the Battle of Three Armies and the two reconcile just before Forest engages in some serious talking.Forest accepts one of the three greasy beans and returns home to his hut a very wealthy giant.

The creepy, English town of Amsterdam holds a secret. Rob Chen has the perfect life working as a police officer in the city and dancing with his admirable boyfriend, Brad Sweet.However, when he finds a solid guillotine in his cellar, he begins to realise that things are not quite as they seem in the Chen family.A bar mitzvah leaves Rob with some startling questions about his past, and he sets off to dirty Amsterdam to find some answers.At first the people of Amsterdam are friendly and courageous. He is intrigued by the curiously brave homemaker, Nadine Gump. However, after she introduces him to hard social media, Rob slowly finds himself drawn into a web of adultery, fraud and perhaps, even cruelty.Can Rob resist the charms of Nadine Gump and uncover the secret of the solid guillotine before it\'s too late, or will his demise become yet another Amsterdam legend
